# WHAT IT IS
#   `tms` is the Rust port + extension of ThePrimeagen's iconic
#   bash `tmux-sessionizer` (~30-line shell script from his
#   dotfiles repo, seen in his tmux/Neovim YouTube tutorials,
#   the script that single-handedly popularized the "fzf into a
#   tmux session" workflow among ~Neovim developers).  Workflow:
#
#     1. tms scans configured search paths recursively for git
#        repositories (and bookmarks)
#     2. it presents them in a fuzzy picker (either fzf-delegated
#        or the built-in ratatui picker)
#     3. on selection, it opens-or-attaches a tmux session named
#        after the directory's basename
#
#   Bind `tms` to a tmux key (`bind-key -r f run-shell "tmux
#   neww tms switch"` in `~/.tmux.conf`) and you have one-keystroke
#   project switching.  Bind `tms windows` to switch tmux windows
#   inside the current session.
#
#   Subcommand surface:
#
#     • tms                          default = open the project
#                                    picker
#     • tms switch                   display OTHER sessions in a
#                                    fuzzy picker with preview
#                                    pane
#     • tms windows                  display CURRENT session's
#                                    windows in a fuzzy picker
#                                    with preview pane
#     • tms sessions                 print running tmux sessions
#                                    (current marked with `*`)
#     • tms start                    initialize tmux with the
#                                    default sessions configured
#                                    in tms config
#     • tms kill                     kill the current tmux session
#                                    and jump to the default
#                                    session
#     • tms rename <name>            rename the active session +
#                                    the working directory
#     • tms refresh [name]           create new worktree windows
#                                    for selected session
#                                    (git-worktree-aware)
#     • tms clone-repo <url>         git clone + create new
#                                    session for the cloned repo
#         --path <dir>               clone-into directory
#         --name <name>              cloned dir name
#     • tms init-repo <name>         `git init` a fresh repo +
#                                    open a session for it
#     • tms bookmark [path]          bookmark a non-git directory
#                                    so it appears in the picker
#         -d, --delete               remove a bookmark
#     • tms open-session <name>      open a specific session by
#                                    name (with dynamic completion
#                                    of available session names)
#     • tms marks                    indexed quick-jump slots
#         list                       list current marks
#         set [index] [-p <path>]    set a mark at index (path
#                                    defaults to cwd)
#         open <index>               open the mark at index
#         delete <index> | --all     delete a mark or all marks
#     • tms config                   manage tms config (all
#                                    fields settable via flags)
#         list [-d, --defaults]      print current config
#         [-p, --paths <paths...>]   search paths
#         [-s, --session <name>]     default-session name
#         [--excluded <dirs...>]     exclude-directory list
#         [--remove <dirs...>]       remove from exclude list
#         [--full-path <bool>]       show full paths in picker
#         [--search-submodules <bool>]
#                                    traverse submodules
#         [--recursive-submodules <bool>]
#                                    traverse submodules-of-
#                                    submodules
#         [--switch-filter-unknown <bool>]
#                                    only show configured paths
#                                    in switch picker
#         [-d, --max-depths <n>]     per-search-path traversal
#                                    depth caps
#         [--picker-highlight-color #rrggbb]
#         [--picker-highlight-text-color #rrggbb]
#         [--picker-border-color #rrggbb]
#         [--picker-info-color #rrggbb]
#         [--picker-prompt-color #rrggbb]
#                                    ratatui picker theming
#         [--session-sort-order Alphabetical|LastAttached]
#         [--clone-repo-switch Always|Never|Foreground]
#                                    post-clone session behavior
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from `src/cli.rs` clap-derive
#                       declarations;  extracted via
#                       raw.githubusercontent.com fetch of
#                       src/cli.rs + src/marks.rs;  every option
